A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Article 1 of Chapter 6 of Title 17 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated,
2 relating to general provisions relative to bonds and recognizances, so as to include
3 aggravated assault as a bailable offense only before a superior court judge; to provide for
4 related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Article 1 of Chapter 6 of Title 17 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
8 general provisions relative to bonds and recognizances, is amended in subsection (a) of Code
9 Section 17-6-1, relating to when offenses bailable, procedure, schedule of bails, and appeal
10 bonds, by revising paragraphs (13) and (14) and by adding a new paragraph to read as
11 follows:
12 "(13) Violating Code Section 16-5-46; and
13 (14) Violations of Chapter 15 of Title 16; and
14 (15) Aggravated assault upon a public safety officer while he or she is engaged in, or on
15 account of the performance of, his or her official duties by the discharge of a firearm."
